<title>BELGIUM: EU clears Siemens/Thomson-CSF venture.</title>
<headline>EU clears Siemens/Thomson-CSF venture.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-07-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Commission said on Monday it had cleared a joint venture between Thomson-CSF and Siemens in the air traffic management business.</p>
<p>The Commission said the two groups would merge their activities in the Air Traffic Management field and Siemens would also contribute to the joint venture, called Airsys ATM SAS, part of its airport turnkey systems activities.</p>
<p>&quot;Although Airsys will be the clear market leader with important market shares in the European Economic Area and in several national countries, it will not achieve a dominant position...,&quot; the Commission said in a statement.</p>
